page.title: 10HOUSING-BOGNOR REGIS
page.content: The few houses on the farming land are widely scattered and most were built over a 100 years ago or more.They have electricity and water supply but most have cess_pit drainage.Some of the houses have been bought by non_farming families e.g. Neal's farm house.In the south east area there is high density housing.Most houses in Rose Green and North Bersted were built between 1911 and 1930.A small area near Grosvenor Gardens and Carlton Avenue was built 1930_1959.The rest of Rose Green and the housing at West Meads was built after 1960.The main house_type is semi_detatched or bungalow.More than 80% are privately owned,have 2 or 3 bedrooms,small gardens and all main services.Many roads have houses or bungalows built in the same style.It is a popular area for retired people.
